cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.NE, cs.SD 

This paper deals with machine translation, specifically addressing the challenge of out-of-vocabulary words in low-resource language pairs. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also discusses the use of neural networks and deep learning techniques, which suggests categories such as cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper involves training and optimization of models, which could fall under cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper discusses the creation of effective parallel corpora, which could be relevant to cs.SD (Sound and Music Computing).
